analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set - Open Label
analysisPopulations.text: This is the set of all subjects who received at least one dose of study treatment during the open label run-in phase.
analysisPopulations.label: FAS-OL
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: This is the set of all subjects who received at least one dose of study treatment during the open label run-in phase.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received >=1 dose of study treatment during open label run-in phase

analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set - Randomized
analysisPopulations.text: This is the set of all subjects who have been randomized at Week 12 and have received at least one dose of study treatment within the double-blind phase. By study design, this will be a subset of FAS-OL. Subjects are assigned to the randomized treatment group regardless of actual treatment received.
analysisPopulations.label: FAS-RA
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: This is the set of all subjects who have been randomized at Week 12 and have received at least one dose of study treatment within the double-blind phase. By study design, this will be a subset of FAS-OL. Subjects are assigned to the randomized treatment group regardless of actual treatment received.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized at Week 12 AND received >=1 dose of study treatment within the double-blind phase

analysisPopulations.name: Per Protocol Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Per Protocol Analysis Set (PPAS) is a subset of the FAS-RA and will include all randomized subjects who did not have any major protocol deviations. The specific criteria for exclusion from the PPAS will be finalized and documented prior to unblinding.
analysisPopulations.label: PPAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Per Protocol Analysis Set (PPAS) is a subset of the FAS-RA and will include all randomized subjects who did not have any major protocol deviations. The specific criteria for exclusion from the PPAS will be finalized and documented prior to unblinding.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Subset of FAS-RA AND no major protocol deviations

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Safety Analysis Set (SAF) is defined as all subjects who receive at least one dose of the investigational product. Safety will be assessed by the spontaneous reporting of AEs, physical examinations, and clinical laboratory results.
analysisPopulations.label: SAF
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Safety Analysis Set (SAF) is defined as all subjects who receive at least one dose of the investigational product. Safety will be assessed by the spontaneous reporting of AEs, physical examinations, and clinical laboratory results.

characteristics.name: Age

characteristics.name: Eczema Area and Severity Index
characteristics.description: EASI score used to define response and flare

characteristics.name: Investigator’s Global Assessment
characteristics.description: IGA score (5-point scale) used to assess disease severity

characteristics.name: Body Weight
characteristics.description: Weight in kg, inclusion criterion requires >=40 kg
